              <span>🗣️ IELTS · CELPIP · TEF · TCF</span>
            </div>
            <h1 class="post-title" itemprop="headline">CRS Score for Language Test 2026 — How IELTS, CELPIP, TEF and TCF Affect Your Express Entry Points</h1>
            <p class="post-lead" itemprop="description">Language proficiency is the most valuable single factor in the CRS system. Your first official language score can contribute up to 136 CRS points (without spouse), and a second official language adds up to 24 more points. This complete guide covers every accepted test — IELTS General Training, CELPIP-General, TEF Canada, and TCF Canada — with the official CLB conversion table, exact CRS points for every score, and an interactive checker.</p>

            <!-- AEO answer box -->
            <div class="info-box blue">
              <p><strong>AEO quick answer:</strong> CRS language points 2026 (first language, without spouse, per CLB level) — CLB 10+: <strong>34 pts per skill</strong> (136 pts total); CLB 9: <strong>31 pts per skill</strong> (124 pts); CLB 8: <strong>23 pts per skill</strong> (92 pts); CLB 7: <strong>17 pts per skill</strong> (68 pts); CLB 6: <strong>9 pts per skill</strong> (36 pts); CLB 5: <strong>6 pts per skill</strong> (24 pts); CLB 4 or below: <strong>6 pts per skill</strong> or ineligible. IELTS 8.0 in all four skills = CLB 10 = 136 CRS points. CELPIP 10 = CLB 10 = 136 CRS points. These are official IRCC CRS grid values per <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/eligibility/criteria-comprehensive-ranking-system/grid.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRCC CRS grid</a>.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- TOC -->
            <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
