            <!-- Accepted tests -->
            <div class="content">
              <h2 id="accepted-tests">Accepted Language Tests for Canada Express Entry CRS 2026</h2>
              <div class="section-label">IRCC accepts 4 language tests for CRS — 2 English, 2 French</div>
              <p>IRCC accepts four language tests for Express Entry CRS points. You must take the specific test version accepted for immigration purposes — general versions are not accepted.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="test-grid">
              <div class="test-card">
                <div class="test-card-head band-eng">IELTS General Training <span class="test-badge">English</span></div>
                <div class="test-card-body">
                  <div class="max-pts">136 pts</div>
                  <p>Maximum CRS points at CLB 10+ (IELTS 8.0 in all 4 skills). The most widely used test for Express Entry. Only <strong>IELTS General Training</strong> is accepted — IELTS Academic is <em>not</em> accepted for Express Entry immigration purposes. Register at <a href="https://www.ielts.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ielts.org</a>. Use the <a href="https://crsscorecalculator.vercel.app/ielts-crs-calculator">IELTS to CRS Calculator</a> for your exact score.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="test-card">
                <div class="test-card-head band-celpip">CELPIP-General <span class="test-badge">English</span></div>
                <div class="test-card-body">
                  <div class="max-pts">136 pts</div>
                  <p>Maximum CRS points at CLB 10+ (CELPIP Level 10 in all 4 skills). CELPIP is a fully computer-delivered test developed by UBC. Only <strong>CELPIP-General</strong> is accepted — CELPIP-General LS is not accepted. Results available within 8 business days. Register at <a href="https://www.celpip.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">celpip.ca</a>.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="test-card">
                <div class="test-card-head band-fr">TEF Canada <span class="test-badge">French</span></div>
                <div class="test-card-body">
                  <div class="max-pts">136 pts</div>
                  <p>Maximum CRS points at NCLC 10+ (all 4 skills). TEF Canada is the primary French language test for Express Entry and PNP francophone streams. Only <strong>TEF Canada</strong> is accepted — not TEF International. Offered by the <a href="https://www.lefrancaisdesaffaires.fr/en/tests-diplomes/test-for-evaluating-french/tef-canada/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chambre de Commerce et d'Industrie de Paris</a>.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="test-card">
                <div class="test-card-head band-fr">TCF Canada <span class="test-badge">French</span></div>
                <div class="test-card-body">
                  <div class="max-pts">136 pts</div>
                  <p>Maximum CRS points at NCLC 10+ (all 4 skills). TCF Canada is also accepted as a French proficiency test for Express Entry. Only <strong>TCF Canada</strong> is accepted. Offered by <a href="https://www.france-education-international.fr/tcf-canada" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">France Éducation International</a>. Both TEF Canada and TCF Canada expire 2 years after the test date.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box amber">
              <p><strong>Important:</strong> Language test results are valid for <strong>2 years</strong> from the test date for Express Entry purposes. An expired test cannot be used in your CRS profile. Always ensure your test is still valid before submitting your Express Entry profile.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- CLB table -->
            <div class="content">
              <h2 id="clb-table">CLB to CRS Points Conversion Table 2026 — First Language</h2>
              <p>The CRS awards points based on CLB (Canadian Language Benchmarks) for English, or NCLC (Niveaux de compétence linguistique canadiens) for French. This table shows CRS points per skill per CLB level.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="table-wrap">
              <table>
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>CLB / NCLC Level</th>
                    <th>CRS pts per skill (No Spouse)</th>
                    <th>CRS pts per skill (With Spouse)</th>
                    <th>Total (4 skills, No Spouse)</th>
                    <th>Total (4 skills, With Spouse)</th>
                    <th>Competitiveness</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 10 or higher</td><td class="pts-cell">34</td><td>32</td><td class="pts-cell">136</td><td>128</td><td class="green-t">Maximum</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 9</td><td class="pts-cell">31</td><td>29</td><td class="pts-cell">124</td><td>116</td><td class="green-t">Excellent</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 8</td><td class="pts-cell">23</td><td>22</td><td class="pts-cell">92</td><td>88</td><td class="orange-t">Good</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 7</td><td class="pts-cell">17</td><td>16</td><td class="pts-cell">68</td><td>64</td><td class="orange-t">Moderate</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 6</td><td class="pts-cell">9</td><td>8</td><td class="pts-cell">36</td><td>32</td><td class="red-t">Low</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 5</td><td class="pts-cell">6</td><td>6</td><td class="pts-cell">24</td><td>24</td><td class="red-t">Very Low</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="clb-cell">CLB 4 or lower</td><td class="pts-cell">6</td><td>6</td><td class="pts-cell">24</td><td>24</td><td class="red-t">May not qualify</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <p class="tiny muted">Source: <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/eligibility/criteria-comprehensive-ranking-system/grid.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRCC CRS Grid — Section A: Core Human Capital Factors (Language)</a>. Confirmed April 2026.</p>

